  "detailed_description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1951140/extras/99e0a523aff418c28d3e1f68fc5ed117.avif?t=1656924675\" width=568 height=115 /></span><br><br>Kaiju is a collection of 2D and 3D audio visualizations ranging from calming waves to clinical spectra and psychedelic fractals.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>It makes waves.</strong></h2>Kaiju listens to your system audio to drive its visualizations in real time. <br>This means music and video streaming services, games, movies and even human voices from VOIP all work to power the effects; it hears what you hear.<br>Alternatively, your microphone can be used to make your voice and the ambience of the room drive the system.<br><br>Kaiju does <strong>not</strong> record any audio or require special permissions. It makes use of Windows' audio APIs commonly used for noise cancellation.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Key Features</strong></h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Real time 2D and 3D visualizations<br></li><li> Works with streaming services, VOIP, games and more...<br></li><li> Themes and modulation of effects</li></ul>",
  "about_the_game": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1951140/extras/99e0a523aff418c28d3e1f68fc5ed117.avif?t=1656924675\" width=568 height=115 /></span><br><br>Kaiju is a collection of 2D and 3D audio visualizations ranging from calming waves to clinical spectra and psychedelic fractals.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>It makes waves.</strong></h2>Kaiju listens to your system audio to drive its visualizations in real time. <br>This means music and video streaming services, games, movies and even human voices from VOIP all work to power the effects; it hears what you hear.<br>Alternatively, your microphone can be used to make your voice and the ambience of the room drive the system.<br><br>Kaiju does <strong>not</strong> record any audio or require special permissions. It makes use of Windows' audio APIs commonly used for noise cancellation.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Key Features</strong></h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Real time 2D and 3D visualizations<br></li><li> Works with streaming services, VOIP, games and more...<br></li><li> Themes and modulation of effects</li></ul>",
